A train crushed a Dangote Cement truck and a tricycle with passengers in Kano State on Sunday. According to reports gathered, the accident  occurred on Obasanjo road in Kano State axis around 11:30am, as the truck was moving on the rail lines with the train speeding towards it. An eye witness stared, “When the driver of the trailer tried to cross the rail line, the train hit the vehicle and the tricycle at the same time.” BBC Radio Presenter Dies Aged 40 In ‘Tragic Accident’ Passengers Injured, Trapped As Train Derails In Lagos However, the number of people injured is still yet undisclosed as they have been taken to the Murtala Muhammad Hospital, Kano.